    "readme": "<div align=\"center\">\n\n# 🎵 SA3 Studio\n\n**A local, GPU-accelerated studio for AI music generation and stem separation.**\n\nGenerate music from text with [Stable Audio 3](https://github.com/Stability-AI/stable-audio-3),\nedit and extend it, then split any track into stems with\n[Demucs](https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs) — all from one Gradio UI.\n\n[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)\n[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)\n[![Code style: Ruff](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-ruff-261230.svg)](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff)\n[![Built with Gradio](https://img.shields.io/badge/built%20with-Gradio-f97316.svg)](https://www.gradio.app/)\n\n</div>\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nSA3 Studio wraps two state-of-the-art open audio models behind a single, friendly\ninterface and adds the production conveniences they're missing — reproducible seeds,\nbatch variations, seamless loops, BPM/key detection, multi-format export, a remix\ndesk, and audio-to-MIDI. Everything runs **locally**; no API keys, no uploads.\n\n## ✨ Features\n\n| Tab | What you can do |\n| --- | --- |\n| 🎤 **Generate** | Text-to-audio with prompt presets, **batch variations** (up to 4), per-result **seed** display for reproducibility, optional **seamless looping**, and automatic **BPM / key detection**. |\n| ✏️ **Edit** | **Audio-to-audio** restyling, **inpainting** (regenerate a region), and **continuation** (extend a track by *N* seconds). |\n| 🎛️ **Stems** | Split into vocals/drums/bass/other (or 2-stem); a **Remix Studio** (per-stem level + mute); one-click **karaoke / acapella** export; and **stem → MIDI** transcription. |\n| 🗂️ **History** | Browse past outputs with playback and the prompt/seed/params metadata stored beside each file. |\n\n**Across the app:** one-click **\"Send to\"** routing between tabs · per-result\n**download** buttons · multi-format export (**wav / flac / mp3**) ·\n**timestamped filenames** (repeat prompts never overwrite) · live **VRAM** readout ·\nruntime **model switching** · **fp16** inference on CUDA.\n\n## 📋 Requirements\n\n- **Python 3.10+**\n- **[uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv)** package manager\n- **(Optional) NVIDIA GPU** — recommended for the higher-quality `medium` model.\n  The `small-music` model runs on CPU.\n- **FFmpeg** — for mp3 export and broad input-format support.\n\n> Models (~1–9 GB) download automatically from Hugging Face on first use.\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/sebastianmanczak/sa3-studio.git\ncd sa3-studio\nuv sync\nuv run python run_gradio.py\n```\n\nThen open the printed local URL (default: <http://localhost:7860>).\n\n### GPU notes\n\nThe project pins the CUDA **cu128** build of PyTorch (see `pyproject.toml`), which\nsupports current NVIDIA GPUs including **Blackwell / RTX 50-series (sm_120)**.\nIf you don't have an NVIDIA GPU, remove the `[tool.uv.sources]` block from\n`pyproject.toml` before `uv sync` to fall back to the CPU wheels.\n\n## ⚙️ Configuration\n\nAll settings live in [`config.yaml`](https://github.com/sebbyrule/sa3-studio/blob/main/config.yaml); every value also has a sane\ndefault, so the file is optional.\n\n| Setting | Default | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `model` | `auto` | `small-music`, `medium`, or `auto` (GPU → `medium`, else `small-music`). |\n| `device` | `auto` | `cuda`, `mps`, `cpu`, or `auto`. |\n| `output_dir` | `outputs` | Where generated audio, stems, and MIDI are written. |\n| `demucs_model` | `htdemucs` | Demucs model variant. |\n| `demucs_segment` | `16` | Demucs segment length (s); clamped to the model's max. |\n| `model_half` | `auto` | fp16 for SA3. `auto` = fp16 on CUDA, fp32 elsewhere. |\n| `output_format` | `wav` | Default export format: `wav`, `flac`, or `mp3`. |\n| `hf_cache_dir` | *(empty)* | Custom Hugging Face cache path (e.g. a larger drive). |\n\n## 🗂️ Project Structure\n\n```text\nsa3-studio/\n├── src/sa3_studio/\n│   ├── config.py        # YAML config + hardware/model auto-detection\n│   ├── generation.py    # Stable Audio 3 wrappers (T2A, A2A, inpaint, continue)\n│   ├── separation.py    # Demucs stem separation (low-level API wrapper)\n│   ├── output.py        # Saving audio/stems, ZIPs, metadata sidecars\n│   ├── audio_tools.py   # Seamless loops, BPM/key analysis, audio→MIDI\n│   ├── run_gradio.py    # Console-script entry point\n│   └── ui/app.py        # Gradio Blocks UI + event handlers\n├── tests/               # Pytest suite (unit + light GPU integration)\n├── docs/ARCHITECTURE.md # Design & data-flow reference\n├── config.yaml          # Default configuration\n└── run_gradio.py        # `python run_gradio.py` launcher\n```\n\nSee [`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`](https://github.com/sebbyrule/sa3-studio/blob/main/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for how the pieces fit together.\n\n## 🧪 Development\n\n```bash\nuv sync                       # installs runtime + dev tools (pytest, ruff)\nuv run ruff check src tests   # lint\nuv run pytest                 # run the test suite\n```\n\n> **Heads-up:** `tests/test_generation.py` and `tests/test_separation.py` run\n> *real* model inference and download weights on first run, so the full suite is\n> slow (minutes) and benefits from a GPU. The `config`, `output`, and\n> `audio_tools` tests are fast and dependency-light.\n\n## 🩺 Troubleshooting\n\n- **`flash_attn not installed` / triton warnings on startup** — harmless. SA3\n  falls back to PyTorch's built-in fused (cuDNN) attention, which is already fast.\n  These messages are silenced at launch where possible.\n- **Out of VRAM** — switch to the `small-music` model (header dropdown or\n  `config.yaml`), or keep `model_half: auto` (fp16) enabled.\n- **mp3 export fails** — install FFmpeg; the app falls back to WAV if it can't encode.\n- **First run is slow** — model weights are downloading; subsequent runs are fast.\n\n## 🙏 Acknowledgements\n\n- [Stable Audio 3](https://github.com/Stability-AI/stable-audio-3) — Stability AI\n- [Demucs](https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs) — Meta AI Research\n- [librosa](https://librosa.org/) · [Gradio](https://www.gradio.app/) · [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/)\n\n## 📄 License\n\nReleased under the [MIT License](https://github.com/sebbyrule/sa3-studio/blob/main/LICENSE). Model weights are subject to their own\nrespective licenses."
